# Turso Database Configuration
# Used for BOTH local development and production (single database for simplicity)
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Install Turso CLI: curl -sSfL https://get.tur.so/install.sh | bash
# 2. Sign up/login: turso auth signup
# 3. Create database: turso db create matt-jones-portfolio
# 4. Get URL: turso db show matt-jones-portfolio --url
# 5. Create token: turso db tokens create matt-jones-portfolio
# 6. Copy .env.example to .env: cp .env.example .env
# 7. Fill in your credentials below
# 8. Run migrations: npx drizzle-kit push
# 9. Import data: node scripts/migrate-json-to-db.js
#
# For production deployment:
# - Add these same environment variables to Vercel

TURSO_DATABASE_URL=libsql://[your-database].turso.io
TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN=your-auth-token-here